HEADWORD: Lunt
<hw>Lunt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>lont</ets>; akin
to Dan. & G. <ets>lunte</ets>, Sw. <ets>lunta</ets>. Cf. <er>Link</er> a
torch.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The match cord formerly used in firing
cannon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A puff of smoke.</def> <mark>[Scotch.]</mark>
<rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

